Nearly every song on the album contains some sort of experimental or [[avant-garde]] quality. "[[The Gift (The Velvet Underground song)|The Gift]]", for example, contains a recital of a [[short story]] and a loud instrumental rock song playing simultaneously, with the former on the left speaker channel and the latter on the right. "[[I Heard Her Call My Name]]" is distinguishable for its distorted guitar solos and prominent use of feedback.
